The worker searched the general area on the trail and spotted a human skull lying approximately 25 feet away. At that time, the worker contacted the supervisor who called 911 and reported the finding to the Bastrop County SO. The sheriff's office conducted a search of the site and found approximately 60 total skeletal elements, as well as apparent human hair with some flesh attached. The skull and mandible with associated dentition were recovered.  Assistance with identification is needed.
